==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] [[Μακεδονία]] (''Makedonia'') "highland", from ancient Greek [[μακεδνός]] (''makednos'')  "high, tall", from Doric Greek [[μάκος]] (''makos'') "height, length" . In Ionian Greek: [[μήκος]] (''mekos'').
In Greek mythology [[Μακεδονία]] (''Makedonia'') was named after [[Μακεδών]] (''Makedon''), the [[patriarch]] of the Macedonians, son of [[Ζεύς]] (''Zeus'') and [[Πανδώρα]] (''Pandora''). ([[Pandora]] was the sister of Έλλην [[Hellen]], the [[patriarch]] of  [[Έλληνες]] [[Hellenes]], "Greeks".)

